    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-10-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-10-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="732"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d732">
                <head>732. Telegram 443 to Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d732fn1">Source:
                        Department of State, Central Files, 611.93/10–1756. Secret; Priority.
                        Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_MWP_1">McConaughy</persName>; cleared by
                        Phleger and Sebald.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1956-10-17">October 17, 1956. 7:09 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d732-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d732-1"/>
                <p>443. For <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>.</p>
                <p>Latest Chinese Communist statement on Geneva talks seems to have fallen flat. Not
                    carried so far by any newspaper or wire service seen here. We plan ignore
                    statement if press continues to do so.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
